Author: azerty21
Title: [ANN][TAEL (WaBi)] - Supply chain, loyalty points, real world adoption
Body: Didn‚Äôt get to run a Walimai masternode? Here is how you can join the queue! Please note before participating: the Walimai masternode queue publicly shows all participant wallet addresses. To join the queue, please get your wallet verified according to instructions here: https://medium.com/@wabiico/how-to-join-the-verified-wabi-holder-discussion-telegram-channel-de891073e6ab  After you‚Äôve verified your wallet address, please fill out the following Google form: https://docs.google.com/forms/u/3/d/1qJXlx3VYPrbB-915nKkSvzie14FUffpP_b0da2M2mUg/  Once you‚Äôve been verified by the WaBi Holder Verification Bot and have filled in the Google form, you are automatically added to the queue!  How will I be prioritized in the queue? Position in the queue will be determined by the number of Supporter Points (SP) that you have.  How are the points calculated? SP is calculated by the amount of WaBi you hold in your registered private wallet. Every day you hold WaBi will give you SP of the same amount. The first date in calculating the points is 30th June 2018 or a date when you moved the WaBis there, whichever is later.  For instance, holding 1023 WaBi in your registered wallet will gain you 1023 SP a day. This means that in 3 days you will have 3069 SP, and will be positioned in the queue accordingly.  Where can I see my place in the queue? The queue will be published, public, and open in July. At that time, you will be able to see your position in the queue at queue.wacoin.io.  What happens if I add more WaBi into the wallet? You will gain SP daily, the total amount based on how much WaBi is in your wallet. Adding WaBi will gain you more SP on a daily basis.  What happens if I remove some WaBi from the wallet? Removing WaBi from the wallet will decrease the amount of SP you gain daily. Additionally, SP will be decreased by the amount of WaBi removed from the wallet, retroactively.  For instance, if you have 3 days of holding 1023 WaBi, you will have 3069 SP. If you remove 200 WaBi, you will only get an additional 823 SP the following day. However, you will also have 200 SP removed for every day previously participated. This means you will have (4 times 823 SP =) 3292 SP after day 4.  What if I have additional questions? You can join us at our official Telegram channel and talk directly to the team: https://t.me/wabi_ico  Alternatively, you can send an email to support@wacoin.io and we will respond as soon as possible.

Author: fishervwb
Title: [ANN][TAEL (WaBi)] - Supply chain, loyalty points, real world adoption
Body: A Tale of 2 Blockchains: WaBi and Walimai  Explaining the what‚Äôs and why‚Äôs of the Blockchains we‚Äôre utilizing.  WaBi‚Äôs Blockchain: WaBi is currently an ERC-20 token and will stay on the Ethereum Blockchain for the foreseeable future. If ETH can no longer cope with the amount of transactions, there will be a migration to an alternative, higher performance Blockchain with all coins being transferred. If ETH technology keeps improving and is able to cope with the volume of transactions we require, it is conceivable that migrating to another Blockchain won‚Äôt be necessary.  WaBi is a consumer incentivization token, rewarding consumers for purchases, scans, and other user related actions. Although our business is related to supply chain operations, we‚Äôd like to stress that WaBi is NOT a supply chain coin. WaBi‚Äôs growth potential expands far beyond Ethereum wallet users and crypto enthusiasts. Because of WaBi‚Äôs function as a loyalty token to incentivize our target demographic in China, we‚Äôre not only tapping into a market of over a billion potential users but also allowing real world usage to those with no exposure to cryptocurrency. WaBi is already being utilized by every day consumers.  Walimai‚Äôs Blockchain: Supply chain transactions through the Walimai retail channel are recorded on our own Blockchain already. Walimai‚Äôs own Blockchain has currently been running in Testnet mode for over a month, with a full migration planned over the course of the summer. There will be no Walimai supply chain coin for this Blockchain as we believe consumer incentivization and marketing is a much better use case. Unlike what is commonly believed, enterprise-grade Blockchain applications do not require coins to operate.  The Blockchain itself is based on Hyperledger software. In the interest of transparency, we‚Äôve decided against utilizing a private Blockchain. We believe that ‚Äòprivate Blockchain‚Äô is an oxymoron, and hold the openness of the Blockchain as an essential feature. Therefore, Masternodes of the Blockchain will function as auditors for transactions on the supply chain. To ensure security, we will only allow reliable auditors to run Masternodes. They will have to deposit WaBi as collateral and will be paid for their work in WaBi. Beyond this, the Walimai Masternodes will function like most other Masternodes.  Specifications for the Walimai Masternodes are being finalized and we will share them when ready. We can say you‚Äôll need a standard Linux server, a cloud based server will also suffice. https://medium.com/@wabiico/a-tale-of-2-blockchains-wabi-and-walimai-385b84db1e0d

This meeting is indicative of the our value proposition to companies we meet with: a safe and streamlined way to sell products in China.  We have finalized the scope of the design work for the Walimai / WaBi rebranding in Q2 of 2018 and the O2O sales terminals which will be installed in Walimai POS in China. Our Business Development Lead for Australia (and the latest addition to the Walimai team), Vadim Mishin, attended FoodLegal‚Äôs FoodFraud Conference and presented Walimai to an audience of national and international industry insiders, speaking about the importance of database development in food technologies and the regulatory frameworks that have the potential to combat food fraud.  We will be expanding our product portfolio to include high demand Australian brands. More specific information regarding the SKUs will be released over the coming weeks.  With the end of March comes the end of the year‚Äôs first quarter. We will be posting a brief recap of Q1 in early April to inform the community of overall progress. Author: giver1975
Title: [ANN][TAEL (WaBi)] - Supply chain, loyalty points, real world adoption
Body: Hi, could someone help me? I participated in the pre-sale of wabi obtaining the pre-wabi. Following the instructions released on the official channels by the company, I joined the buy-back in part and held a part for lock for 3 months. At the time of the Buy back the link to the lock was not available yet. In the following days I had to leave for work (my job and on ships), when I returned after 14 days my dashborad no longer worked. I promptly contacted some of the staff who first answered via email asking me with what mail I would have made the KYC. From that moment on I did not receive any more answers. I would like to point out that my KYC has been accepted by another 15/20 ICO and 6/7 exchange. It does not seem right to me that my tokens are lost or rendered unusable. My transactions are all demonstrable and the staff of a successful ico should find a solution especially for those who believed in advance in the project and team participating in the pre-sale, taking all the risks of the case.  I await information  Thank a lot  Giver

Author: netnutter
Title: [ANN][TAEL (WaBi)] - Supply chain, loyalty points, real world adoption
Body: Respect! I respect people who do their fundamental analysis before going for an investment. I couldn't agree with you more about the fact that some parts of the whitepaper are rather blurry. I am also observing and trying to understand some areas of the project that are not clear to me. Once I get my answers then probably I am going to invest. On the whitepaper it says that the users work as miner by scanning and verifying the products. But they have failed to elaborate on that. My understanding is by scanning the product users are timestamping and updating the Geolocation  of a certain product. So basically the users are kind of verifying the manufacturers claim. But the whole purpose and use of 'block-chain' is rather abstract! On the flip-side, speaking from experience, almost all the Asian projects are notorious for ambiguity at the beginning. Gradually they tend to overcome those issues. I have sent emails and messages and waiting to hear from them. If I find new info that might be helpful, will defo share with you.

Title: [ANN][TAEL (WaBi)] - Supply chain, loyalty points, real world adoption
Body: Dear BitCoinTalk Community,  Apologies for the radio silence on the forum as of late. Since the ICO we‚Äôve been working overtime to ensure everyone received their WaBis, and that their excess funds were refunded. But now it‚Äôs time to get back to growing the business and focusing on developments that will benefit us all.  For those who missed it, we‚Äôve recently released a progress update on Medium which you can find here: https://medium.com/@wabiico/wabi-project-progress-update-18th-dec-2017-6735d7ae141c  After some debate, we have decided to focus our WaBi and Walimai related marketing efforts on a select few channels. We invite you all to find us on our official Telegram channels, follow our Twitter account for the latest updates, join the discussion in our subReddit, or sign-up for our Newsletter at wacoin.io.  The above channels are the ideal ways to stay up-to-date on WaBi and Walimai related news, and we hope you‚Äôll join us as we continue to grow.  We will no longer update our BitCoinTalk thread, so please redirect questions to the channels above or reach out to us at support@wacoin.io.  Sincerely, WaBi Team

Author: Kayth
Title: [ANN][TAEL (WaBi)] - Supply chain, loyalty points, real world adoption
Body: Great product from WALIMAI and probably very usful and successful... but why the hell they need a crypto coin for that? They write because:  - Single-click automatic payment for Walimai protected products (at current exchange rate if the user has insufficient WaBi) - Paying with WaBi grants additional benefits: discounts, improved delivery terms, bonus WaBi points with every purchase - Allows users to buy loyalty points in bulk with discounts  Seriously... do you guys think that these chinese mothers will pay for their baby food with WaBi? I cannot imagine... maybe once when crypto get's standard and when it doesn't matter anymore which coins I have, because they get converted automatically to the desired currency at payment time. But this is still far future... Discounts, loyality points... We all know this from our favourite supermarket chain. Would you buy coins of them just because they are on blockchain now? Probably not...

Author: George_Token_Jr
Title: [ANN][TAEL (WaBi)] - Supply chain, loyalty points, real world adoption
Body: Hey guys, I‚Äôm doing some math here and it doesn‚Äôt add up. Could you clarify something for me?  The whitepaper says:  a) Up to 10.000.000 will be sold at the preICO at 0.03 USD/coin price. Funds will be used to launch the ICO. Up to an additional 1.000.000 coins will be distributed through the bounty program. b) Up to 40.000.000 will be distributed at the ICO stage in November 2017. 80% sold to ICO contributors, 20% distributed among the team and bounties. Funds will be used to grow sales in baby stores, add more product categories (such as alcohol) and set up the WaBi Project blockchain based, remotely hosted loyalty system. c) The remaining coins (49.000.000 if all 10.000.000 are sold at the preICO, 1.000.000 are distributed as bounties at the preICO round and 40.000.000 are sold during ICO stage) will be reserved to be delivered to consumers through the mining process. Consumers will receive coins by purchasing Walimai protected products and participating in other activities. These 49.000.000 will be held in an escrow. A merchant (seller of products protected by Walimai technology) will be entitled to release WaBi coins equivalent of 5% worth of quarterly increase in sales of his products, from the escrow into circulation by distributing these coins among the customers in the form of rewards and discounts. These coins can not be sold by merchants at an exchange.  a)   3.700.000 tokens were sold, 6.300.000 remaining b)   80% out of 40.000.000 is 32.000.000 ‚Äì crowdsale, 8.000.000 distribution among team members and partners. c)   Remaining coins ‚Äì 49.000.000 (+6.300.000 not sold during the pre-sale).  So, if I understand correctly, max of 32 mln coins can be sold during the crowdsale.   In their last Telegram post Wabi guys say:  Tokens price: We sell WaBi tokens at 0.25 USD per token (the higher end of the range we announced previously). This will give us around 11.5m USD raised (after accounting for ~50% preWaBi buyback).  11.500.000/0.25= 46.000.000 At least 46m tokens must be sold during the crowdsale if you don‚Äôt account for the buyback. How do you come up with this number of tokens? If you include 6.3m unsold pre-ico tokens and 8m that are meant for the team and the partners, then it‚Äôs 46m indeed. But does this really correspond with what‚Äôs laid out in the whitepaper? In my understanding ‚Äúup to‚Äù means ‚Äúno more than‚Äù. Could the team elaborate on this, please?

Author: ngin-x
Title: [ANN][TAEL (WaBi)] - Supply chain, loyalty points, real world adoption
Body: Guys, as someone who has participated in many ICOs since 2016 and know how the market works, I caution you against investing in this ICO because:  1) Lately each and every single ICO that gave presale investors anything over 10-20% discount has dumped below ICO price. There are no exceptions. Even wildly popular ICOs like AirSwap and Request Network are now below ICO price because of this. Less popular ICOs are almost 50-70% below ICO price now. Wabi gave presale investors almost 850% discount (3 cents pre-sale vs 25 cents ICO). I leave it to you to guess what will happen when this token hits the exchanges.  2) This is not a very popular ICO. There is almost no hype around this project, so you will have a really difficult time finding buyers for this token and also 99% chance this won't be listed on any major exchange.  3) Don't be fooled by pre-sale investors claiming they believe in this project and will buy more at the ICO. This is a common con used by people to lure unsuspecting buyers into buying a token at hyper-inflated prices because they need buyers to dump on afterall.  4) The Walimai app this company is building the project around hardly has any reviews or ratings or downloads on the Google Play Store. So it's not a proven business as they claim to be.  Only invest in this ICO if:  1) They agree to lock up all pre-sale investor tokens for 3-6 months without exceptions.  or  2) They agree to reduce the ICO price to 3 cents which should make it a level playing field for everyone.  Lastly, I would like to end by saying that it is upto each and every one of us to demand higher standards from ICOs. If we continue to support ICOs that screw ICO investors by giving presale investors discounts, we will continue to take losses and investing itself will become non-viable. My advice is to wait for the token on the exchanges. You will most certainly be able to purchase it at 5-10 cents as opposed to 25 cents.

Author: WaBiWalt
Title: [ANN][TAEL (WaBi)] - Supply chain, loyalty points, real world adoption
Body: WaBi ICO starts 28th of November at www.wacoin.io | Whitelist + individual caps. ÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºç 1) ICO details:  28 of October: KYC registration starts at www.wacoin.io. Participants who pass KYC will be added to the WhitelistÔºé 21st of November - Whitelist closedÔºé  USD 0.25 per tokenÔºé 46,000,000 tokens for sale. USD 11,500,000 hard capÔºé Total supply: 100,000,000 tokensÔºé  An individual cap will be applied on the first day of the ICO. It will be doubled on day 2 and doubled again on day 3. If not all WaBis are sold by then, we will remove the caps from day 4 onwards.  ÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºç 2) KYC: starts on 28th of October at www.wacoin.io  To participate in our token sale, you will need to pass KYC. We will require: - Full name - Citizenship(s) - Photo/scan of your government-issued ID which states citizenship. Passports will be accepted. Decisions on all other documents will be made on a case-by-case basis and will result in delay - Selfie of you holding the submitted ID document - Email - Mobile phone number - ETH address to which we can send the WaBi tokens (you need to have control of this address, e.g. it can not be an exchange address)Ôºé  Participation restrictions:  Unfortunately we will need to restrict certain groups of people: - Nationals of the People‚Äôs Republic of China - US persons (US citizens, US residents, green card holders), if they don‚Äôt have an accredited investor status. You will need to prove your accredited investor status through a 3rd party vendor that we are working with - Persons under 18 years of age We don't like to restrict people from participating in our sale but we also need to comply with relevant regulations and protect the project from any legal risks.  ÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºçÔºç 3) PreICO tokens buyback: We will announce exact details of the process for both options a) and b) soon.  There‚Äôs been a lot of fear of tokens being 'dumped' by the preICO contributors. We are making an offer to all preICO participants that will completely eliminate the problem.  In essence the offer to preWaBi holders is: EITHER a) To lock tokens for 3-6 months and get 5-10% bonus (coming out of the founders‚Äô personal allocation) OR b) Sell preWaBi back to WaBi Project at 8.5USD/preWaBi or 0.25USD/WaBi (reflecting the 1:34 preWaBi to WaBi ratio).  This way, whatever 'dumping' might occur will be absorbed by the project and not the ICO contributors at the exchange.  All tokens bought back by WaBi project will be held as a reserve for at least 6 months.

Author: WaBiWalt
Title: [ANN][TAEL (WaBi)] - Supply chain, loyalty points, real world adoption
Body: If you believe that the WaBi will plummet after entering the exchanges, by all means, feel free to wait. However, we'd ask you to consider more than one factor when making this decision:  1. We didn‚Äôt have a private pre-sale. We did a public Pre-ICO which resulted in a wide distribution of tokens with very small amounts held by any given individual investors. Please see for yourself: https://ethplorer.io/address/0x753af9dbe862fdb00db5bc9455063e3aad3674bd#tab=tab-holders&pageSize=100  2. Exchanges do not have KYCs and, as noted in our whitepaper, we explicitly excluded certain nationalities for ICO participation, in addition to people who would not want to go through the KYC process.  3. Aside from the ICO, we are a rapidly growing company with constant business developments. I realize that this factor often gets lost in the crypto world due to the scarcity of projects with anything more than a vapourware promise. But this is by far the most important factor influencing the market cap, in the non-crypto world.

Body: Dear Bitcointalk community,  Since the announcement of our bidding system during our Q&A, we‚Äôve been getting a lot of feedback from our communities. We‚Äôre happy to see many who appreciate our project and we understand that many of you would rather see us conduct our ICO in a more familiar format.  We also realize that not all of the supporters are active in the groups, so, to get a more complete understanding we will run a poll via email. We will ask you a simple question on whether you prefer the bidding system or a standard whitelist.  If you have not yet signed up for our emails, please, do so now, so that you could participate in the poll. You can do so at www.wacoin.io  The poll will be closed within 24 hours and only takes few seconds to respond, please do take the time to fill it in.  Thank you all!

Author: WaBiWalt
Title: [ANN][TAEL (WaBi)] - Supply chain, loyalty points, real world adoption
Body: Hey guys, here's a small update from the founders about the upcoming WaBi ICO!  Hey everyone at Bitcointalk!  - We have launched our offline terminals in 3 baby stores in China last Sunday, so Walimai protected milk formula is currently being sold both offline and online.  - Our team is growing and we now have dedicated community managers as well as a highly experienced marketing director. We have been branded a ‚Äòhidden ICO‚Äô by some reviewers, however, our major marketing activities will start within the next 2 or 3 weeks. We are expecting the channels to become much more lively.  - At the moment we are finalising the ICO participation model. As we stated previously, we think that the current ‚ÄòBlack Friday at Walmart‚Äô model is terribly resource-inefficient, favours all sorts of sea mammals, and leaves the bulk of people unhappy. We are also not big fans of forced rationing. Therefore, we are finalising a system which hopefully can eschew most of these ailments. We shall be publishing a demo-version in the next few days so that everyone here can practice and get familiar with.  - We realise that currently the regulatory environment has been somewhat turbulent and a lot of people wonder how are we being affected.   - Firstly, to reconfirm, we are in full ICO preparation mode at the moment. The ICO goes ahead. You shall be seeing a lot more updates both here and elsewhere over the coming few weeks.   - Secondly, the China Ban. Just wanted to reiterate that it does not affect us directly, as we are running the ICO out of Singapore. We were bound to introduce a few changes to the Wabi circulation rules when it comes to China. However, once again, neither the business model nor the token model has been affected in a major way. We shall be publishing an updated Whitepaper soon, where these special provisions are presented in a more detailed manner.   - Finally, we wanted to tentatively designate November 7th as the ICO start date, subject to final confirmation. We realise that it is a bit later than we originally envisaged, however, due to the regulatory changes were compelled to move it. We are confident that this date leaves us enough time to step up our marketing efforts and to raise awareness to a sufficient degree to make our ICO a success.  - Last but not least, we welcome any feedback you might have.  Yas, Alex, and the Wabi Team  Beyond the message, we'll be providing everyone with the latest info when we update the wacoin.io website later this week  Please let me know if you have any questions!

Author: WaBiWalt
Title: [ANN][TAEL (WaBi)] - Supply chain, loyalty points, real world adoption
Body: Our situation is a little bit more nuanced than that. Some people will probably sell tokens as they hit the exchanges. But keep in mind:  1. We sold 20% of circulating supply (10% of total) at the preICO to raise money to run the actual ICO.  2. Assuming half of those coins are sold on exchange quickly after the ICO - it is 10% of the circulating supply.  3. That would push the price down, we don‚Äôt know by how much, maybe around 10% but it depends on a lot of other factors.  4. 10% price volatility in crypto is a daily thing. It‚Äôs noise.  The above argument is not 100% rigorous but helps to put things into perspective.  We would also encourage people to think of the unmet demand that will be filled at the exchange: a lot of people will not pass our KYC (some countries restricted for the initial sale, some people will not be able to provide the right documents, etc). They will probably try to get the tokens at the exchange.  Most importantly, we would encourage people to look at the project long-term, not based on the first few days when it‚Äôs on the exchange.

Author: albusxx
Title: [ANN][TAEL (WaBi)] - Supply chain, loyalty points, real world adoption
Body: Dear contributors,  After the recent announcements by SEC (US Securities and Exchange Commission) and MAS (Monetary Authority of Singapore) regarding the regulatory position towards the ICOs (link below) we are compelled to significantly alter the structure of the Wabi token. We realise that such alteration in the middle of the fundraising round is far from ideal and we understand that you may want to reconsider your decision to contribute based on the new information, therefore we are offering a full refund for every contributor who is not happy with the change in the structure of the Wabi token, returning 100% of the funds in the same currency as well as reasonable transaction fees.  Before we fix the new model Yaroslav and myself will speak to our community in Slack, Telegram as well as inform every contributor via registered email in order to answer potential questions and collect feedback. We find the conversations we‚Äôve had so far with our community extremely valuable and often eye opening. Thus, in the coming few days we shall be fine-tuning the model based on the feedback we receive. We plan to fix the new model on Monday 14th August after incorporating your feedback.  Reasons for the change: 1.    With clarification by the Singaporean authorities our previous model of the Wabi token would almost certainly be considered a security. This creates significant risks for the project, our investors as well as ourselves. 2.    The feedback that we received so far was overwhelmingly in favour of us not limiting ourselves to the baby-store model and, instead, positioning it like an open platform with different channels, products and regions. Although this may increase the complexity of the project, in the long run we believe it has a far greater potential.  New WaBi (ËõôÂ∏Å) model:  1.    WaBi (ËõôÂ∏Å) coin will be structured as a crypto-token that can be used to purchase Walimai protected products (in some way similar to loyalty programme points). This includes not only baby food, but also alcohol, cosmetics or any other products we plan to protect with our technology.   In terms of geography it will start in China but will expand to other regions as well, even though exact timing it‚Äôs hard to predict at this stage.   This will also not be limited to products that we sell ourselves: we plan to add other companies to the platform (this was always part of the overall Walimai plan). These companies will join the Wabi rewards system as well.  2.    We will encourage the use of the Wabi tokens in several ways: a) We will setup a seamless user interface. An Example: https://cldup.com/ciIWwsikEO.png (215kB)  b) Allow users to ‚Äúmine‚Äù tokens with a proof of purchase. Basically, buyers of products protected by Walimai technology will receive some initial coins when they start buying. We are reserving some coins at the ICO specifically for that.  c) Get overall better terms. This may include discounts, special offers etc., discounted purchases of WaBi (ËõôÂ∏Å) coins etc.  New coin parameters: 1.Total supply of WaBi (ËõôÂ∏Å) will be limited at 100.000.000. With the following split: a) Up to 10.000.000 will be sold at the preICO at 0.03 USD/coin price. Funds will be used to launch the ICO. Up to additional 1.000.000 coins will be distributed through the bounty programme.  b) Up to 40.000.000 will be distributed at the ICO stage in September/October 2017. 80% sold for 0.15-0.25 USD/coin, 20% distributed among the team, bounties, founders. Funds will be used to grow sales in baby stores, add more product categories (such as alcohol and cosmetics) and set up a seamless WaBi usage process for consumers.  c) The remaining coins (49.000.000 if all 10.000.000 are sold at the preICO, 1.000.000 are distributed as bounties at the preICO round and 40.000.000 are sold during the ICO stage) will be reserved to be delivered to consumers through the mining process. Consumers will receive coins by purchasing Walimai protected products and participating in other activities. These 49.000.000 will be held in an escrow. A merchant (seller of products protected by Walimai technology) will be entitled to release WaBi coins equivalent of 5% worth of quarterly increase in sales of his products, from the escrow into the circulation by distributing these coins among the customers in the form of rewards and discounts. These coins can not be sold by merchants at an exchange.  Here is an example explaining point (c): merchant H sells cosmetics with Walimai protection, H used to sell 1m USD/month of cosmetics and grew sales to 1.3m USD over a quarter. Suppose, at the same time the price of WaBi at an exchange is 10 USD. H will then be eligible to distribute (1.3m-1m)*5%/10=1500 WaBi to it‚Äôs current or future buyers. And all of these WaBi have to be used by the merchant to encourage the use of WaBi and acquire additional users. These coins will be kept in several escrows for security.  2. We will get listed on exchanges after the ICO as planned before.  Why we believe WaBi tokens will be a success:  1.    Natural demand for the token. As it will be used within the loyalty system there will be a growing non-speculative transaction volume that will back the token circulation and ensure user adoption  2.    Large underlaying market. It‚Äôs not just baby stores now. It‚Äôs baby food, cosmetics, alcohol or other products that would be protected with Walimai label. And not only our own sales but sales of future partners: producers, distributors etc. 3.    Real customer benefit and seamless utilisation process. As a blockchain based loyalty system it will be much more advanced to whatever is currently available on China‚Äôs market.  Next steps for you: 1.    You should make the decision if you wish to remain or withdraw from the project. It will be possible to withdraw until the end of Sunday 20th August London time. 2.    If you decide to continue participating - nothing needs to be done. At the end of preICO we will exchange preWabi tokens that were already purchased to WaBi not at the 1:2 rate but at 1:34 rate, reflecting the 1 USD price of preWabi and 0.03 price of WaBi. 3.    If you decide to withdraw - let us know via an email to alex@wacoin.io. Please, use the same email that you‚Äôve used to register at wacoin.io. We will ask you to send the preWabi tokens back if you already received them. And process the refund within 24 hours after receiving them back.  We hope you will give this a good considerations. We have updated the website and WP (all available at www.wacoin.io) to further describe the new approach. We are happy to answer any questions you might have.  Also, we plan to extend the preICO by two weeks. Working on the new model we could not really take care of the marketing well enough. These additional two weeks will enable us to collect more at the preICO but will not delay ICO or exchange listing because we will already start to prepare for the ICO itself.  Alex and Yaroslav  Links to the announcements: SEC https://www.sec.gov/oiea/investor-alerts-and-bulletins/ib_coinofferings https://www.sec.gov/news/press-release/2017-131  MAS http://www.mas.gov.sg/News-and-Publications/Media-Releases/2017/MAS-clarifies-regulatory-position-on-the-offer-of-digital-tokens-in-Singapore.aspx

Author: Obi2024
Title: [ANN][TAEL (WaBi)] - Supply chain, loyalty points, real world adoption
Body: Walimai System is very robust against ‚Äòlabel-cloning‚Äô attacks Below is a demonstration of system robustness in face of ‚Äòlabel cloning‚Äô attacks. Scenario I: Sophisticated attacker / Supply Chain NOT Compromised: System response: geo-location data fails to match failing authentication Scenario II: Sophisticated attacker/ Supply Chain Compromised (counterfeiter is able to place products in designated locations)*. ‚ñ™ If the product is not taken out of circulation: There is a timegap in cloning and placing the object in circulation (which typically requires several days) and the next customer scanning the original object (which in FMCG typically takes minutes) changing the pairing conditions thus prohibiting authentication ‚ñ™ If the product is taken out of circulation: In order for it to make economic sense the counterfeiter needs to either sell the fake object at a price premium to the original (which is a counter sense) or create multiple copies of the object. However, scanning one such counterfeit product will desynchronise the rest of the batch, thus invalidating any further matching attempts and making the product unsalable.  from the WP Page 9, That is good

Author: albusxx
Title: [ANN][TAEL (WaBi)] - Supply chain, loyalty points, real world adoption
Body: Thanks for the question. Please, see below: Main preICO terms PreICO and ICO ‚Ä¢ We will run this in two stages: first preICO, then ICO itself. PreICO will enable use to put together an ICO that is adequate to the size of the project and opportunity.  PreICO ‚Ä¢ Timing: start on 28th July at 17.00 Shanghai time and run for 21 days or until reaching maximum amount of 300k USD equivalent ‚Ä¢ Minimum and maximum amounts are 30k USD and 300k USD equivalent. If we don‚Äôt reach 30k, the contributions will be returned. The preICO will be closed if/when we receive 300k USD equivalent in contributions ‚Ä¢ Token: token is called preWaBi. Each preWaBi will be sold at 1 USD equivalent during the preICO. Each preWaBi will be converted into 2 WaBi at the end of main ICO ‚Ä¢ Token parameters: ERC20 token standard, 330.000 issued at the beginning of preICO. 10% of tokens on top of whatever is bought by contributors will be distributed as bounties. PreWaBi tokens not distributed to contributors or as bounties will be destroyed. No tokens will be distributed among founders or the team. E.g. if we receive 100k in contributions, 100.000 tokens will be distributed to contributors, 10.000 tokens will be distributed as bounties. The remaining 220.000 tokens will be destroyed. ‚Ä¢ Our preICO wallet will be secured with 2 out of 3 signature payments requirement, signatures will be held by founders and a team member. We are not securing it with a 3rd party due to relatively small amount of the raise. ICO wallet will be secured by 3rd party escrow. ‚Ä¢ Accepted currencies: BTC, ETH, LTC . ‚Ä¢ Once minimum amount is reached (30.000 USD equivalent) we will start converting into fiat currency to avoid fluctuation risk as most of the expenditures to run the full ICO will be in fiat currencies. ‚Ä¢ The amount of preWaBi delivered to contributors will be fixed at current exchange rates at the time when we receive the payment but delivery of preWaBi will be done at the end of preICO. ‚Ä¢ PreICO token code can be examined at (link to Github will be added later)  ICO ‚Ä¢ Important to note that we are still in discussion with lawyers on some of the parameters of the ICO. Hence it is possible that some of the ICO terms may change even after the preICO. At the same time will do our best to try and change it as little as possible as well as to protect the interests of our contributors and ensure they are not coming out worse off with whatever change of the below parameters. ‚Ä¢ Timing: start in August or September, will last for 30-60 days or until reaching maximum amount ‚Ä¢ Minimum and maximum amounts are 500k USD and 30m USD equivalent ‚Ä¢ Token: token is called WaBi (ËõôÂ∏Å). Each WaBi will be sold at 1 USD equivalent during the ICO ‚Ä¢ Token benefits: the collected contributions will be used to build sales network of products with Walimai labels through baby shops in China. Products will be sold at a 5-25% margin because of additional security, 60% of the profits made will be distributed to WaBi token holders (subject to taxes) every year. Will will distribute the profits in one of the following ways: a) buying back WaBi tokens at an exchange b) direct transfers to all of the WaBi token holders. For more detailed explanation please see the legal setup and benefits distribution part of this document ‚Ä¢ Token parameters: ERC20 token standard, tokens will be issued only one time at the end of the ICO following the formula: amount of issued tokens=‚Äúcontributed funds‚Äù/0.7+(preWabi issued at preICO)*2. For example, if 100k USD is contributed during preICO and 7m USD is contributed during the ICO, 7m/0.7+100k*2=10.200.000 WaBi tokens will be issued. 7.000.000 tokens will be distributed among the contributors, 3.000.000 will be distributed as bounties, team and founders compensation and 200.000 will be used for conversion from preWaBi into WaBi. ‚Ä¢ Some of the WaBi tokens may be sold at a discount during ICO, e.g. with a discount for early contributors, in this case we will use the nominal value (1 USD) for the above calculation. ‚Ä¢ Given the parameters outlined above, the maximum amount of WaBi tokens can reach 30m/0.7+300k*2=43.457.143 ‚Ä¢ Our ICO wallet will be secured with multi signature account involving 3rd party escrow. More details will be announced closer to the ICO ‚Ä¢ Accepted currencies: BTC, ETH, LTC

Author: neonloop
Title: [ANN][TAEL (WaBi)] - Supply chain, loyalty points, real world adoption
Body: The problem of fakes in the West may sometimes seem like a 'theoretical' problem that only tangentially touches the everyday life. At least you are not worried about buying plastic rice when you go grocery shopping. In China, however, the problem is present literally everywhere.  Here are some examples of what it looks like:  Fake beer:  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kXIFdRugGtw  And no, they are not washing the cans, it is actually the 'beer' that they use to fill up the cans  Fake brandy:  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bpb-w4Uz5I4  Fake eggs:  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jXIokJLu_zE  Fake rice:  https://edrugsearch.com/plastic-rice-from-china/  Therefore we started with baby-formula since due to its high marginality it has been one of the favorite products among the counterfeiters resulting in numerous scandals involving a lot of infants dying or sustaining severe afflictions.

Title: [ANN][TAEL (WaBi)] - Supply chain, loyalty points, real world adoption
Body: A WABI can solve China's fake? The key is to promote the use.

Author: albusxx
Title: [ANN][TAEL (WaBi)] - Supply chain, loyalty points, real world adoption
Body: Exactly! Good technology is not enough here, it's important to get people (who are generally not that tech-savvy) to start using the technology. That's why we are starting with baby food segment. Mother really care about the safety of the food, especially after all of the scandals. And in smaller cities (like Jiaxing, Hefei, Jiaozuo etc) there are not many options to buy baby food and feel safe, unlike in Shanghai where you can go to an expensive City supermarket and can be reasonably sure what you are buying is not fake.  Getting mothers/fathers to use this on baby formula is only the first step. Next it would be to add other products/segments like alcohol and pharmaceuticals. And, because doing the project with baby food is profitable, it will give us enough momentum to raise funds (investors will love to see profitability in the baby food segment) and make it successful in other segments as well.
